FYI: time is 2PM PACIFIC 4PM CENTRAL (the Reel has the time zones flipped)
——————————————————
It is happening AGAIN! @reneefordmetals and I are going LIVE 2PM PST/4PM CST TOMORROW! That’s Thursday, the day before Friday! 
Come hang out with us in our studios and join the conversation where we will be talking about my 2023 Dated Studio Planner for the Jewelry Artist (my shipment arrived from the publisher so they are ready to SHIP!) and Hold-IT, Renee’s amazing soldering clay. I think she may even DEMO! But don’t hold me to that. 
Less of a sales pitch and more just a casual hangout for metalsmiths and jewelry artists. Have questions to ask either of us? Bring them to the Live. 
See y’all SOON!

Far, FAR too effing early for this crap.  But here we are.
We drove to SeaTac last night at rush hour in the most asinine blizzard conditions to get our jet setter son off to sunnier destinations (needless to say, I am envious). It was absolutely one of the most stressful drives I’ve done in the 30 years I’ve lived here. It rivaled WYO blizzard driving conditions except with Seattle area traffic. I do not recommend it. Zero stars.
BUT the good news is Paul and I made it home safe and Cody is soaking in the sun much closer to the equator as I type this.
@reneefordmetals and I are going Live right here on IG in a few hours, 2PM Pacific, 4PM Central. Our IG post/story yesterday has the time zones swapped, so take note.
Grab something warm to drink and come hang out with us. Bring your questions and we will answer as many as we can ❤️⚒️

It’s HERE! Ready to ship!
•2023 Studio Planner for the Jewelry Artist•
This is the third edition of the dated planner. This edition is updated with new cover graphics and more of the pages that so many of you asked for including more grid sketch pages and custom order pages. 
The two videos in this post show off what’s inside this newest planner. I’m pretty excited about this one. Lots of great new additions including studio inspiration ideas sprinkled throughout the Weekly Planning section.
This is the only print run of the 2023 planner that I will be doing. I have about 33 available as of tonight. Once these are gone, they are gone. Order soon so you don’t miss out!
To order, click on the product tag on the images in this post or visit my IG profile for a direct link to the planner listing on my website.
Any questions drop them below or direct message me.
I have decided to offer international shipping pensively… it is crazy expensive to ship outside of the US, so be forewarned ❤️⚒️

Littles! 
I’ve spent a bunch of time this week making little jewelry. I realize this holiday season shoppers are having to really pay attention to where they are spending and how much they are spending. 
I’m meeting y‘all where you are at with a great variety of super affordable jewelry that is perfect for gift giving. Earrings, pendants and more are coming with me to @olympiafarmersmarket tomorrow and to @olynightmarket on Thursday evening this coming week! Come out and see what is new ❤️⚒️
(I am only at the farmers market on Saturday this weekend as I am attending a royal frosting cookie decorating class on Sunday!)

Is it time for ice cream yet?
Of course it is. Any time is time for ice cream.
I’m wrapping up my week in the studio. I’m going thru a spell that once I am out here I don’t want to leave. I just want to be my introvert self, sit at my bench and make things. I don’t want to be a sales person, a customer service rep, a smiling face. But alas, life calls.
See you at market tomorrow. I think the sun might make an appearance even if it’s going to be cold as butts.

I played hooky from the @olympiafarmersmarket today to do THIS! I took a royal frosting and cookie decorating class with Deana of @sweetlittlethingsbakerytenino 
and OMG it was an absolute BLAST! If you ever get the opportunity to take a class from her…. DO IT! I plan on putting my new skills to work over the coming weeks to make cookies for the holidays (and beyond)! I have always wanted to do this and my one earlier attempt when Code was a wee babe was an epic fail. 
As much as I hate the “self care” blah, blah, blah trope, I am making damn sure I take time to do things that I want to do. I am not getting any younger and I feel like now there is not enough time to get to all those things I have put off because of my business or what ever other excuse I have used in the past. Ain’t getting outta here alive. Time to have some FUN!

I’m doing one last @olynightmarket Holiday event this coming Thursday!
Festivities begin at 4pm. So many benefits to this amazing venue most of which include an amazing array of local makers/small businesses but also the fact it’s INDOORS, WARM, and don’t forget: COCKTAILS!!
Santa will be there from 5PM - 7PM enjoying the evening and offering great photo ops for you and your family. 
A few of my favorite artist makers will be there including @andiclarkejewelry and @kiki_crystals and @olysudz 
Come on out to Lacey from 4PM to 9PM, Thursday Dec 8th

It’s MONDAY! 
Back in the studio making jewelries.
Feeling tall and lofty today, well, in a design sense…. I’ll never, myself, be accused of being tall and/or lofty. I am more short and stocky like George Costanza…
But I digress… I wanted a bit more atmosphere in my latest pieces and here’s what I’ve come up with the so far.
As earlier stated, you can find me this Thursday at the @olynightmarket Holiday event and then back at the @olympiafarmersmarket on Saturday and Sunday. #shoplocalfortheholidays #shopolympia #olympiafarmersmarket #olynightmarket #buyart #giveart

Finally (almost) DONE!
These somewhat ametrine amethyst points are super close to being ready for their forever homes. Just need clasps and a final spit and polish (totally kidding on the spit part… or am I? 😂).
As always anything purple is absolutely impossible to photograph. So I’ve done my best with the crap ass lighting Winter affords us mossy folk in the PNW. First two slides are in natural “the sun’s about to set at 3PM” light and the second two slides are under my super blindingly bright bench light.
These will be coming with me for the @olynightmarket this Thursday evening unless someone messages me here to snap ‘em up.
Questions? DM me.
💜⚒️

Tonight is the night! Come out to @ricardos.kitchen for the Holiday @olynightmarket from 4PM to 9PM! You will find the space filled to the brim with movers and makers ready to help you mark things off your gift giving list. Santa will be on hand for photos from 5PM -7PM!
There’s a BAR! And that means….. COCKTAILS!
I have spent this week getting everything ready for this special event. Pulling last minute things together this AM and tossing a quick Reel together before I pack up the 4Runner and head north! Hope to see you this evening.
Oh, guess what else? It’s INSIDE, WARM and doesn’t cost a thing to enter. ❤️⚒️🎄
Not a bad alternate set up if I do say so myself.  @olynightmarket has such an amazing venue and the Holiday version is absolutely delightful! We are here until 9PM so still time to come down!

Best laid plans and such…
Today was supposed to be a bench day meaning I would actually sit and MAKE things. 
Well, THAT did not happen. But I did take some time to tame the absolute disaster of a bench top.
So, your turn. Show me your bench and tag it #showmeyourbench Be sure to tag me so I can share your beautiful disasters.

Literally the extent of any Yule decorating around here: 
PINK TWINKLE LIGHTS. 
FTR they are staying up year round.
And I REALLY need to get to work making things. But I am super distracted. Obviously.

Now that’s more like it!!!
I want to wrap everything in pink twinkle lights, grab a folded blanket, shove it in a laundry basket and lay down in it and look up at the magic.
I did that as a little girl under the Christmas tree. Way back when, when all I cared about was when the Sears Toy Catalog would arrive and my brothers and I would pore over it making our Christmas lists… all of us with over hyped expectations but hardly ever truly disappointed when the big day finally arrived.
But, many decades later I am far too big for the laundry basket, there’s no more Sears Toy Catalog and this time of the year makes me feel pretty meh.
Oh well, there’s still pretty things like pink twinkle lights to enjoy and, also, wine.

“How much you wanna make a bet I can throw a football over them mountains?...” 
- Uncle Rico
——————————————————
Reticulated some silver and created a mountain range for a special project I spent the day working on. Can’t show you the finished piece for a bit, however. 
——————————————————
I will be at the @olympiafarmersmarket this weekend both Saturday and Sunday and then back for the Last Minute Shoppers Delight December 22nd -24th for those last minute gifts you know you have forgot…
——————————————————
Hope your day finds you happy and well.

Made a bit of a unexpected trip to SeaTac to drop a certain Big Lebowski looking character off for a flight to Vegas. When I was getting ready to sit in traffic for 3 hours on the trip home my mountain made a quick appearance!
——————————————————
I am no way ready for market tomorrow but I’ll be there with a few new things. This week was a bit of a shit show… but there’s one regular weekend left of the holiday market and the Last Minute Shoppers Delight Dec 22nd-24th at the @olympiafarmersmarket and I plan to be there for all days, or, at least, until I run out of inventory 😎

I didn’t get much made this week but I did get a bunch of tree rings made including these little Sparkly Night Sky adjustable rings. I have… I think 7 available in an assortment of sizes (one of these shown is already spoken for).
I will also have a bunch of my In The Forest Pine Tree rings with me as well in various sizes at the @olympiafarmersmarket this weekend. 
All of these rings ship easily and *might* arrive in time for Christmas (but ZERO promises). Message me for details. 
❤️⚒️

What’s better than homemade Snickerdoodles?
Literally nothing.
———————————————
After freezing my 🍑 off all day at market today, I slogged home, ate a bunch of weird random carbs plus spicy chicken noodle soup for dinner. Oh and a fair amount of cookie dough. Raw. With eggs. I live dangerously, my friends… if someone was to die from eating raw cookie dough, well, let’s just say there are far worse ways to go out.
ANYWAY, I DIGRESS.
Vendor holiday potluck at market tomorrow. And who wants to bring healthy food to something like that? Not this girl. So, I made what just might happen to be my best batch of snickerdoodles of my ENTIRE LIFE. @casadia_terroir be ready, my friend….

I have been a member of the @etsymetal team for over 10 years. I could likely spend a good chunk of time telling you about all of the benefits being a part of this amazing group offers.
But what I REALLY want to tell you about is that each year we do a Secret Santa gift exchange. And each year I get incredible jewelry from an artist in our group. And this year, well, this year I pretty much struck gold as the person who sent to me I have LONG admired her amazing work. @robinwadejewelry is not just an incredible jewelry artist, but she draws, she paints and she does ceramics. And she excels at ALL OF IT. And each piece of art she creates is filled with such heart and soul. I urge you to follow her, if you don’t already.
And look at what she sent me!! My SOAR pieces are instantly my new favorites. There’s some deep meaning behind them and they are the gift I really needed at this point in time. Thank you, Robin, my dear metalsmith friend. You have made this girl incredibly happy. ❤️⚒️

Okay @instagram I’ll play; I used a pre-made 2022 Reels template to highlight pictures/videos I took over the last year set to IG selected music and IG selected timing. Have to say it was easy and quick. Seeing that Italy was the year’s (okay, lifetime..) highlight, I chose a bunch of random moments, in no particular order. I could have picked 100’s more if they had let me…
I can’t wait to go back.

SOLD OUT!! Thank you!!
Please note: you may get your books in two shipments. Don’t be alarmed if your shipment only contains one book! The other one will be there soon!
You can sign up for email updates when planners and bundles are available on my website 😎⚒️
—————————————————
For some time now @reneefordmetals and I have been mulling over the idea  to offer a bundle deal on our publications. I am happy to announce it is FINALLY happening!
Presenting the 2023 Studio Planner for the Jewelry Artist and Wanderlust Dust Ring Tutorial booklet bundle for $69!
Why not start the new year off getting your studio life organized AND learn epic new skills?  Here’s an easy way way to do both 😎
While I would love to write some super funny and quirky copy to help sway you to add these to your collection, my right brain is on hiatus after a week of solo life and dog caretaking. So instead I’ll just say click the product tag in the images and visit the website for details on what’s inside each book in this bundle.
One thing I do want to mention - you save $26 when you buy this bundle. Full price if each book was purchased separately would be $95 (before shipping, that is).
Any questions, just holler. Sooner you order the quicker we will get them to you because new year is just over a week away! ❤️⚒️

Head’s up! I had full intention of being at all three days of the Last Minute Shoppers Delight this week starting tomorrow at the @olympiafarmersmarket however I was not expecting the high temperature to only be 26°.
That just flat out does not work for me. Pair that with the expected ice storm that is likely to hit us late Thursday into Friday morning so we are going to say  Friday is looking iffy for my attendance as well. 
Saturday? It’s anyone’s best guess. I’ll keep you posted here…
Stay warm, my friends. It’s gonna be a long night. The longest of the year, in fact.

We survived the nasty ass ice storm and while the promised “big warm up” they swore was going to be here by now hasn’t happened, Code and I still made it to @left_bank_pastry to pick up my Bûche De Nöel AND SURPRISE, a couple of cinnamon sugar cronuts that we promptly inhaled.
How is THAT for a run on, nonsensical sentence??
Anywho, I WILL be at the @olympiafarmersmarket tomorrow, Saturday, December 24th for ONE LAST DAY of the Market’s Last Minute Shoppers Delight. Swing by the market from 10AM to 3PM to grab those last on the list gifts. I made a few more of my Sparkly Night Sky rings and a few REALLY cute studs that are getting polished up as I type in the steel shot tumbler. Weather *should* be about 30° warmer than it has been (but I won’t totally buy that until I see it..).
This will be my last weekend at the market for a few weeks. I am taking a MUCH needed respite to give my soul a chance to regroup and recharge. I’ll be back on Saturdays starting in the later half of January.
Happy Holidays, Merry All, and Thank You for being here with me, I am grateful for you and your support. ⚒️❤️

My sweet, stubborn Samson, my heart is broken. I don’t have the words right now to express all of the sadness and love spilling out of my heart but Samson is free from his shackles of his diabetes ravaged body. He is free and basking in the sun rays. I love you, punkin’ pie. Always.

I’m tending to my crushed heart, distracting myself the best I can…it’s been a rough day.
———————————————
But to try and get back to some sort of a semblance of routine I’m going to share a few things I made this last month that were gifts so I couldn’t show them until the holiday was in the rear view mirror…
Here’s the first: malachite azurite druzy (stone from @azurz ) paired with a hand pierced reticulated mountain range on a wide sterling band. 
The stone has tiny little green sparkles that you can catch a glimpse of in the video on the last slide.

I made it out of the house today. As much as I wanted to sit and doom scroll to avoid all things, I know that’s not what I REALLY want to do. I want to get back on track and back in the studio. Easier said than done, BUT I did it.
I’m working on a super small collection of fun little stacker rings and studs. And maybe a few more one of a kind stone pieces. Or not. I don’t know when the exact website release date will be, but you can stay tuned here or sign up for my email updates on my site (link in my profile).
Hope your week is going better than mine. Thanks again for all of the well wishes ❤️⚒️

<Sound on for commentary>
Sure I could have done a time-lapse video so it would fit into IG’s stupidly short time allowance on videos/Reels but I do what I want. So here’s two 3 minute and change videos broke down into many 1 minute and change slides. I will beat you at your own game, Instagram (shakes fist  at the sky)!
As a member of @lionpunchforge Product Development team I get my hands on new tools before anyone else! Come along and see what was inside today’s shipment; it was packed with new tools, Product Development Team swag and STICKERS!
Because unboxing is pretty much a one shot chance when videotaping, I stumble on names and I’m not always great at making sure things are in shot of the camera. Eh, what are you gonna do? I’m an artist, not a video content maker. Questions, drop them in the comments. If I don’t have the answer, I will find it out for you. 
Thank you, Chris, it was nice to have something really great show up on my door step today. The pick-me-up was much appreciated ❤️⚒️

From a rough brainstorming sketch to finished bracelet. I changed the design along the way, I think, for the better. This was a special order (yeah, I know, I know. I sometimes can’t say no) that I had fun creating as it combines my piercing designs with techniques I don’t typically do together. The three scenes represent three siblings, from oldest to youngest. I have made many pieces for several members of this family so I feel I have grown to know them over the years. They hold a special place in my heart ❤️⚒️🌲

Today was a bezel day. Because that’s all the energy my head had the capacity for. The hits just keep coming.
Two weeks ago Paul left for Vegas to be close to his Dad who’d just under went emergency surgery. His dad got thru the surgery but had a hard time recovering. Unfortunately he passed away early this morning.  So needless to say, this week has not been an easy one by any stretch. 
——————————————————
I’ve known Jim since I was 15. We met under uncomfortable circumstances but he never held it against me. Well, actually I suppose I should say if he did, he never showed it. With a sharp wit and a wicked sense of humor he rarely said much but when he did say something you listened closely. You had to because he talked quietly and with intention. He was proud of Paul and even prouder of Cody. The tough walls would crumble when he spoke of either. I will miss him. And my heart breaks for Paul and his siblings. My hope is if it’s true a soul moves forward, that Jimmy, his eldest son, was there waiting for him to help him to whatever is next. 
🛩️👨‍✈️🔭🏛️🏎️
Send Paul and his family some love, if you would. ❤️💔❤️

Today was a good day. And surprise, the Space Needle is PINK.
Not sure how they knew but I’m glad they did 💖

Ushered in the first day of the new year out in the forest. Paul made it back home yesterday after two weeks of being gone. I am so glad to have him back even if everything is weighed down by sadness. Time will smooth those edges but for now we just do those things that help make things a little less heavy.  Being out under the mossy canopy of the towering trees helps dull the ache a little for the both of us.
I hope each of you have a better coming year than the last. May kindness find you. 
I’m grateful for you all. Thank you for being here for me. ❤️⚒️

A few more gifts I made back in December. A pair of camas earrings, a wren pendant and a garlic pendant. You know, the (un)usuals… all hand sketched and pierced with my saw.
I’m taking a little time off from the market and from my typical studio hours over the next few weeks. The downtime was planned long before all of the tough events last week and, boy, am I glad I planned for it. I am using some of this time to work on the latest edition of the Undated Studio Planner AND I am also working on a sister project to the Studio Planner. Not quite ready to spill the beans on that but if you watch the upcoming IG Live with @reneefordmetals this Saturday you just might be the first to know what’s brewing 😎⚒️

I think this is the last of the gifts I made that I took pictures of. Did I get any photos of it finished? No. No, I most certainly did not.
———————————————
Made for a young lady I have watched grow up over the last 7 years who is now a skilled horse enthusiast - an extra small western saddle stirrup. She’s a girl after my own heart. I grew up around horses and I was happiest when I was in the horse paddock. 
This one was extra special to make 🐴🐎

Moody (read: depressing AF) winter light makes for some challenging photography. Spent the afternoon taking some new jury shots and while nothing worked out as planned and I will need a repeat to try again, I did get some photos that should be fine for the website if I ever get around to getting ready for a new collection release like I had planned… time will tell on that.
@olympiafarmersmarket is back open starting tomorrow for Winter Market. Now thru March the market is open 10AM to 3PM Saturdays only. 
With all that said, however, I am not back until next Saturday, January 14th.
❤️⚒️

Top Five Tools and other shenanigans.
Thanks everyone who stopped by to watch and learn about @reneefordmetals and I’d favorite hand tools. We give shout outs to @imp.gen @pepetools_usa @riogrande  and @eurotool_inc 
Next Live we will cover the glorious madness of our upcoming Tucson gem show trip.

I finally set up a new email update link on my website which is available for all who would like to be notified when the newly updated Undated Studio Planner for the Jewelry Artist is available for pre-orders. And as I discussed in the IG Live with Renee earlier today I am also going to be offering a Studio Companion planner which will have all the great features of the studio planner with out the pesky “planning AKA calendar pages.” Which means more sketching pages, more design layout pages, more custom order pages AND, newly added stone inventory pages and more! Both versions of these planners will be available soon to pre-order. If you would like to be notified when they are ready, please visit my website and sign up for email updates. 
Any questions, just drop them below!
(Image in this post is shown for reference only. The updated Undated planner will have new graphics 😎❤️⚒️)

FINALLY at the bench working after nearly two weeks away. Took an act of congress to get me out here today, but I made it. Geeesh!
Have had a few new design ideas rattling around including more lofty archway pieces. The idea to engrave the continuation of the mountains came as I was finishing up the piercing. Yes, I realize I should have waited to engrave it until AFTER it was oxidized and tumbled in #honeandhighlight because the bright finish the graver gives those extended mountains is pretty near perfect…. But I’ll know better next time!
Plan is to be back to the @olympiafarmersmarket this Saturday, January 14th and hopefully have some fresh new pieces! ❤️⚒️

Made one more… and yes, still engraved it before I oxidized. Thinking one side will have oxidized engraved lines which continues the dark line of the design and the flip side will have bright cut engraved lines. Maybe. Because if I slip while doing the engraving after it’s all oxidized and tumbled, I am screwed. I’ll see how I feel once these are to that point.
❤️⚒️

It’s that time of year. Art festival applications are open and it’s time to apply for summer shows. It also means it is time to freshen up jury photos with more recent work and try to make this set of photos more attention grabbing than the last. It is also my least favorite part of this business. Fighting winter light, my dark hibernation mood and worse, a wicked case of impostor syndrome after getting rejected from a show I’ve done several years in a row last year. 
This set of circumstances makes it really hard to get all this tackled in any sense of urgency let alone happily.
Blerg. Anyone else feeling pissy? Raise your hand 🙋🏻‍♀️

So everyone can recognize the simple little daisies on the left, right?
Anyone want to take a guess as to what the design next to the daisies is? I obviously had a specific blossom in mind… not easy to translate into simple minimal lines so if you can’t figure it out that’s okay, too 😂💜⚒️

Let me tell you… this week has been quite a year.  I snuck in quite a few studio hours but not as many as I had hoped. Today we capped off the week with Paul’s much anticipated surgery to get his guts back where they belong. He came thru with flying colors and is relaxing for the next several days while I toil away… just kidding! But I WILL be at the @olympiafarmersmarket tomorrow, Saturday, January 14th. 
I’ll have several new pendants, earrings and some cute stacker rings. Come spend the day at the market ❤️⚒️

Cookie decorating class number two!!
SO MUCH FUN. Spent the afternoon learning even more fun decorating techniques in my second class with Deana. Even perfected my royal icing consistency knowledge and I feel like I am even better prepared for my next at home cookie batch.
Deana is such an amazing instructor. Patient as the day is long and a wealth of knowledge, I highly recommend her classes to anyone looking to try out a new, and more importantly, addictive creative skill. 
And look at how adorable my cookies turned out! Even the one I accidentally stuck my finger into when the icing was still super wet 😂
Be sure to follow @sweetlittlethingsbakerytenino to watch for her class postings 💜

@lionpunchforge Ti Tweezy titanium tweezers have become a must-have for making quick work of stacker ring soldering. Standard steel tweezers are a complete heat thief, stealing away the necessary heat from the torch. These titanium tweezers allow all of heat to stay directed on the task at hand.

A new IG Live is happening tomorrow, Friday, January 20th at 5PM PST/7PM CST!
Renee and I will be talking everything TUCSON!
Desert sun, gemstones, In-N-Out Burger and more! We lay it all out from our favorite shows, our favorite sellers and more. Have burning questions, we might just have answers 
😎🏜️🌵☀️💍💎 ⚒️❤️

Restocking some best sellers! Tiny pine tree pendants will be all finished up and with me tomorrow at the @olympiafarmersmarket 
I made round and rectangle options with various tree counts on each.

(CHANGE OF PLANS): no market for me today. I’ll be back February 11th!

Winter Market is happening January thru March, every Saturday from 10AM to 3PM.
Come spend the day with us! ⚒️❤️

TUCSON 2023 PLANS! @silentgoddess and I chat about our favorite shows and sellers. Laney will tag the sellers in the comments. Feel free to ask questions about anything we covered and didn’t cover! We will be at @pepetools_usa booth Thursday 2/2 demoing and hanging out with @lionpunchforge and showing off Hold-It! Soldering clay and all kinds of tools you are gonna want to take home. Come say Hi!

❤️⚒️

Mini Icons Collection is LIVE! 
I am blown away by the early response (THANK YOU!!) but there’s still many more fun pieces waiting for YOU.
Visit my profile for the link to my website. You can navigate to the Mini Icons Collection from the front page by clicking on the image that looks like the one in the post.

I want to give the biggest shout out and an ever so humble THANK YOU to those of you who shopped the Mini Icons collection over the last 24 hours. Everybody’s order has shipped minus the one traveling with me to the desert (you know who you are 😎).
There is still a selection of Mini Icon pieces available and I’ve included a few photos of some of those here in this post. To shop just visit the link in my profile.
I’ll be shipping thru out this week up until I am on an airplane headed south to the land of gems, desert sunshine, cactus and best of all family 🏜️🌵☀️🧡

On a break….
I leave for Tucson this weekend and meanwhile I am not in the studio and not coming to market until I’m back from Tucson. It’s a typical Winter situation for me. I kinda hunker down and take some time to think/focus just on things other than my business this time of the year. I need to do things NOT jewelry related to reset my mental health a bit. Plus winter is a tough time for me emotionally. I basically have to just survive these real dark months and that usually means kinda checking out from the self employment small business grind for a spell.
But I’ll be back at it in a few weeks. Tucson has a way of recharging my creative batteries. Sunshine and gemstones pretty much fix anything ❤️⚒️

@cclarkb5 and I did three days worth of touristing in 12 hours today. We did so many cool things BUT the highlight was the petroglyph hike. Cody and I hiked about 1.5 miles up a rocky wash/riverbed (UPHILL 😅) scrambling up some “moderate” rocky parts keeping our eyes open for the the drawings until we reached the mother lode!

I have been a car fanatic since I was a little kid. I wanted to be a race car driver when I grew up but living in Cheyenne, Wyoming didn’t exactly afford many opportunities for budding race car drivers, let alone female ones. Such is life. But my love of cars has never waned. I took Auto Shop in high school, and next to art classes it was by far my favorite elective. When I met Paul he was a mechanic and even he marveled at how I could tell, just by seeing tail lights or headlights, what type of car it was in the dark. See, I have many talents 😂
I’m a decent mechanic on pre-90’s cars yet i’m not bad at diagnosing new car troubles either. Google obviously helps in nailing down specifics nowadays.
Anyway, added to my tool collecting proclivities, I also collect tiny cars. If given endless garage space and a bottomless wallet, I would collect full size cars but well, I don’t have either of the above. So I stick with the small ones.
I lean towards pretty specific ones with a very big soft spot for Lancia Delta. Before Italy when I actually was able lay actual eyes on my Holy Grail of cars (see last image), my only Delta sightings were in photos and Hot Wheels. This past Friday I was able to add to my tiny Delta collection by nabbing metal flake dark green one. I’d say it looks pretty happy next to the others on my bench.
So there you have it. A little bit more about me that goes beyond jewelry and cookies.

D’oh! 
I was SO GD EXCITED to order and receive my heavy duty metal foot controls for my Foredom and Grobet flex shaft motors. I ordered them while I was in TN, came home and stalked the tracking info, waiting with bated breath for the knock on the front door announcing their arrival after their week long trek from the other coast, directly east of us.
Hastily I sliced open the outer box,  tossing bubble wrap haphazardly to the floor, removed the two pedals and readied them to replace the crappy plastic default controls that I’ve been using for decades.
My excitement was palpable. I grabbed the cord, plugged one end into the power strip and then grabbed the one that connects the motor to the foot control…. But. But…… Nooooooooooo. What is this foreign connection? What is happening?? 
Hopes dashed. Reality set in. My haste bit me in the ass. Pulling up the @gesswein.jewelry site on my phone, I realized my mistake. I had ordered the first ones that popped up when I searched the site. Not paying attention to the description that stated these were for the H style motors. NOT the SR motors, which I have. Damn it. Much cursing was done. Today I packed those incorrect pedals up and took them to UPS. Came home and ordered the RIGHT ones. Once all is said and done, I will have paid about $80 in shipping alone to get the wrong ones to me and back to the East coast then the right ones to me. 
Lesson here? READ THE DESCRIPTION. You have no one to blame but yourself if you don’t.

These are super tedious but also a blast to make. Each one starts as a pencil sketch on painters tape stuck to silver sheet stock, then I trace over the design with a sharpie so I can see the lines. Holes are drilled and the piece is sawn out bit by bit. Findings are soldered on, and little dangles are drawn up, sawn and soldered just as the main pendant. Everything still needs to be oxidized and tumbled. I’ll be photographing these before they come to market with me and that might not happen until next week. We’ll see.

Not only is @reneefordmetals my ride or die Be Fri she is also the source for one of the coolest (or hottest? 🤔) soldering tools in the metalsmithing industry: Hold-It - The Moldable Third-Arm ™️ soldering clay!
No, she didn’t pay me or even cajole me to post this, I am happy to share it because it makes chain making a breeze. Well, more of a breeze; chain making is a bitch of a task, but Hold-It makes it SO much easier to solder your chain links more efficiently. 
I formed a small amount of the clay into a long rectangle and pressed the links into it to hold them upright. Did my soldering then carefully removed the soldered chain and repeated the process with additional sections of the chain.
I reused this same molded clay form 5 times. The used clay can be saved and reconstituted to be used again at a later time (it’s important to remove and discard any dark or burnt clay).
If you have any questions, drop them in the comments!
Hold-It is available on Renee’s website: www.reneefordmetals.com

Remember this one? I soldered a backplate to the mountain impression piece but first I prepped a setting for a stone. Adding a little flush set stone solved a potential dangerous situation: you never want to solder something together completely with an open space in the middle. If there is nowhere for the hot air to escape when soldering the pieces together the risk of a tiny yet dangerous explosion is high. Adding a little “star” CZ to the sky was a perfect solution as I drilled the hole for the setting before I soldered everything.
Wasn’t going to oxidize this one but decided it needs it because the shiny finish just doesn’t do the mountain  scene justice. But that is a task I am leaving until next week.
